articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: A surface-to-surface missile fired at central Israel from Yemen hit an unpopulated area, causing no injuries, Israel's military said on Sunday.
articles.title: Missile fired from Yemen set off sirens in central Israel, military says

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: At least 30 people, including three children, were injured when a Russian guided bomb hit a high-rise residential building in Kharkiv in northeastern Ukraine on Sunday.
articles.title: Russian bomb injures at least 30 civilians in Ukraine's Kharkiv, officials say

articles.author: Gram Slattery, David Ljunggren
articles.description: Law enforcement officials said during a press conference that the gunman was in some bushes near the property line of the golf course when Secret Service agents spotted a rifle barrel.
articles.title: FBI investigating another attempted assassination of Trump

articles.author: David W Cerny, Marek Strzelecki
articles.description: One person drowned in southwest Poland and thousands were evacuated across the border in the Czech Republic after heavy rain continued to batter central Europe on Sunday, causing flooding in several parts of the region.
articles.title: Floods claim two more casualties as torrential rain batters central Europe

articles.author: Douglas Gillison
articles.description: The FBI said on Sunday it was assessing the credibility of threats against Haitians at Wittenberg University following baseless claims by Republican presidential candidate Donald Trump that the migrants in the town were eating cats and dogs.
articles.title: FBI looking into anti-Haitian threats at Springfield, Ohio, university

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Typhoon Bebinca made landfall in Shanghai on Monday morning as a Category 1 storm, the most powerful tropical cyclone to directly hit the Chinese financial hub in more than seven decades.
articles.title: Typhoon Bebinca lands in Shanghai, strongest storm to hit city since 1949

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Eight people have died trying to cross the Channel from France to England, French authorities said on Sunday, confirming earlier media reports.
articles.title: Eight die in Channel crossing attempt, French authorities say

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Mali, Burkina Faso and Niger will introduce new biometric passports as part of their withdrawal from a West African bloc in favour of a new Sahel alliance after military leaders seized power in all three countries, Mali's leader said on Sunday.
articles.title: Mali, Burkina and Niger to launch biometric passports under new alliance

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: China has freed David Lin, a U.S. pastor who had been in jail since 2006, the State Department said on Sunday, marking the release of a man who Washington claims was wrongfully detained.
articles.title: China frees American pastor who US claims was wrongly jailed, State Dept says

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: British Prime Minister Keir Starmer has promised "a new era" in cross-border cooperation to tackle people smuggling gangs ahead of talks on Monday with Italian Prime Minister Giorgia Meloni, part of his push to reset Britain's relations with Europe.
articles.title: UK PM Starmer pledges migration cooperation ahead of Italy talks
